#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "&appname; Details"
msgstr "&appname; Podrobnosti"

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "Field Types"
msgstr "Vrste polj"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each collection may have an unlimited number of fields. &appname; supports "
"eleven types of fields, which allow for a range of different data."
msgstr ""
"Vsaka zbirka ima lahko neomejeno število polj. &appname; podpira enajst vrst "
"polj, ki omogočajo vrsto različnih podatkov."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid "Simple Text"
msgstr "Preprosto besedilo"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The most basic field type is called <emphasis>Simple Text</emphasis>. No "
"restrictions are placed on the field values, and the data entry widget is "
"the standard line edit. This type is appropriate for fields which aren't "
"expected to have long values, such as the author or the genre."
msgstr ""
"Najosnovnejša vrsta polja se imenuje <emphasis>Enostavno besedilo</"
"emphasis>. Za vrednosti polj ni nobenih omejitev, gradnik za vnos podatkov "
"pa je standardno urejanje vrstic. Ta vrsta je primerna za polja, za katera "
"se ne pričakuje, da bodo imela dolge vrednosti, kot sta avtor ali žanr."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid "Number"
msgstr "Število"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:26
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>Number</emphasis> type is identical to the <emphasis>Simple "
"Text</emphasis>, except that the data is restricted to being numerical. "
"Entries will be sorted numerically in the column view if a <emphasis>Number</"
"emphasis> field column is clicked. The standard line edit, with small arrow "
"buttons for increasing or decreasing the value, is used for data entry. No "
"formatting is ever applied."
msgstr ""
"Vrsta <emphasis>Število</emphasis> je enaka vrsti <emphasis>Enostavno "
"besedilo</emphasis>, le da so podatki omejeni na numerične. Vnosi bodo "
"razvrščeni številčno v pogledu stolpcev, če kliknete stolpec polja "
"<emphasis>Število</emphasis>. Za vnos podatkov se uporablja standardno "
"vrstično urejanje z majhnimi puščičnimi gumbi za povečanje ali zmanjšanje "
"vrednosti. Oblikovanje se nikoli ne uporabi."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "&URL;"
msgstr "&URL;"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <emphasis>&URL;</emphasis> type allows for links to other documents, "
"using the standard &kde; file type associations for opening the linked "
"documents. No validation is done on the actual value of a <emphasis>&URL;</"
"emphasis> field, but non-valid links are not opened. The data entry is a "
"line edit with a button for opening the standard File-Open dialog, but any "
"&URL; may be used. Relative &URL;s are interpreted relative to the location "
"of the data file, once it has been saved."
msgstr ""
"Tip <emphasis>&URL;</emphasis> omogoča povezave do drugih dokumentov z "
"uporabo standardnega &kde; povezave vrst datotek za odpiranje povezanih "
"dokumentov. Dejanska vrednost polja <emphasis>&URL;</emphasis> se ne "
"preverja, vendar se neveljavne povezave ne odprejo. Vnos podatkov je "
"urejanje vrstice z gumbom za odpiranje standardnega pogovornega okna File-"
"Open, vendar kateri koli &URL; se lahko uporablja. Relativni &URL;-ji se "
"interpretirajo glede na lokacijo podatkovne datoteke, ko je ta shranjena."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <link linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>Entry Editor</interface></"
"link>, the label becomes the link, while in the <link linkend=\"entry-view"
"\"><interface>Entry View</interface></link>, an actual hyperlink is used. "
"This field type is convenient for linking to <acronym>PDF</acronym> files of "
"bibliographic entries, or to movie reviews, for example. No formatting is "
"ever applied."
msgstr ""
"V <link linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>urejevalniku vnosov</interface></"
"link> oznaka postane povezava, medtem ko v <link linkend=\"entry-view"
"\"><interface>pogledu vnosa </interface></link>, je uporabljena dejanska "
"hiperpovezava. Ta vrsta polja je priročna za povezovanje do <acronym>PDF</"
"acronym> datotek bibliografskih vnosov ali na primer do filmskih ocen. "
"Oblikovanje se nikoli ne uporabi."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Relative &URL;s may also be used. They are interpreted relative to the "
"location of the &appname; data file. In the <link linkend=\"entry-editor"
"\"><interface>Entry Editor</interface></link>, the line edit provides auto-"
"completion for local file locations. If you want the &URL; from the &kde; "
"File Selector Dialog Box to be interpreted relative to the document "
"location, then a property for the &URL; field should be set to "
"<emphasis>relative</emphasis> : <emphasis>true</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Uporabijo se lahko tudi relativni &URL;. Razlagajo se glede na lokacijo "
"podatkovno datoteko &appname;. V <link linkend=\"entry-editor"
"\"><interface>urejevalniku vnosov</interface></link> urejanje vrstice "
"omogoča samodejno dokončanje za lokalne lokacije datotek. Če želite &URL; iz "
"&kde; Pogovorno okno izbirnika datotek, ki se razlaga glede na lokacijo "
"dokumenta, nato lastnost za &URL; mora biti polje nastavljeno na "
"<emphasis>relativno</emphasis> : <emphasis>true</emphasis>."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "Paragraph"
msgstr "Odstavek"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For longer text fields, the <emphasis>Paragraph</emphasis> type offers a "
"larger text edit area, and is always in its own category. A "
"<emphasis>Paragraph</emphasis> field may not have multiple values, nor is it "
"automatically formatted. It cannot be used for grouping. Abstracts, plot "
"summaries, or reviews should be entered using this field type."
msgstr ""
"Za daljša besedilna polja vrsta <emphasis>Odstavek</emphasis> ponuja večje "
"območje za urejanje besedila in je vedno v svoji kategoriji. Polje "
"<emphasis>Odstavek</emphasis> ne sme imeti več vrednosti, niti ni samodejno "
"oblikovano. Ni ga mogoče uporabiti za združevanje. Povzetke, povzetke "
"ploskev ali ocene je treba vnesti s to vrsto polja."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Line feeds are replaced by an HTML break to ensure consistent formatting. To "
"disable this replacement, add a property for the field with a value of "
"<emphasis>replace-line-feeds</emphasis> : <emphasis>false</emphasis>. Spell-"
"checking can be disabling by setting a property with a value of "
"<emphasis>spellcheck</emphasis> : <emphasis>false</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Znaki line feed so nadomeščeni s prelomom HTML, da se zagotovi dosledno "
"oblikovanje. Če želite onemogočiti to zamenjavo, dodajte lastnost za polje z "
"vrednostjo <emphasis>replace-line-feeds</emphasis> : <emphasis>false</"
"emphasis>. Preverjanje črkovanja lahko onemogočite, če nastavite lastnost z "
"vrednostjo <emphasis>spellcheck</emphasis> : <emphasis>false</emphasis>."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choice"
msgstr "Izbira"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When a field should be limited to a few preset values, a <emphasis>Choice</"
"emphasis> type is used. The acceptable values are presented in a drop down "
"box for selection. Multiple values can be allowed. Fields such as "
"bibliography type or personal rating are <emphasis>Choice</emphasis>-type "
"fields."
msgstr ""
"Ko mora biti polje omejeno na nekaj prednastavljenih vrednosti, se uporabi "
"vrsta <emphasis>Izbira</emphasis>. Sprejemljive vrednosti so predstavljene v "
"spustnem polju za izbiro. Dovoljenih je lahko več vrednosti. Polja, kot je "
"vrsta bibliografije ali osebna ocena, so polja tipa <emphasis>Izbira</"
"emphasis>."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Semi-colons should be used to separated the allowed values."
msgstr "Dovoljene vrednosti ločite s podpičji."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checkbox"
msgstr "Potrditveno polje"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For fields which take a yes or no value, the <emphasis>Checkbox</emphasis> "
"type is available. By default, the field is toggled off. <emphasis>Checkbox</"
"emphasis> fields are not formatted and are limited to single values. "
"Internally, the field values are carried as <emphasis><constant>true</"
"constant></emphasis> or <emphasis><constant>false</constant></emphasis>. "
"Some examples are gift or loaned fields."
msgstr ""
"Za polja, ki imajo vrednost da ali ne, je na voljo vrsta "
"<emphasis>Potrditveno polje</emphasis>. Privzeto je polje izklopljeno. Polja "
"<emphasis>Potrditveno polje</emphasis> niso oblikovana in so omejena na "
"posamezne vrednosti. Interno se vrednosti polja prenašajo kot "
"<emphasis><constant>true</constant></emphasis> ali "
"<emphasis><constant>false</constant></emphasis>. Nekaj primerov so darila "
"ali izposojena polja."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:115
#, no-c-format
msgid "Date"
msgstr "Datum"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <emphasis>Date</emphasis> field can include a day, month, and year. The "
"date is shown in the standard format of YYYY-MM-DD, which allows for easy "
"sorting. The standard &kde; Date Selector may be used to choose the date "
"with the mouse, or it may be entered directly. The field is not required to "
"have non-empty values for the year, month, and day; only the year may be "
"entered, for example. Multiple values are not allowed."
msgstr ""
"Polje <emphasis>Datum</emphasis> lahko vključuje dan, mesec in leto. Datum "
"je prikazan v standardni obliki LLLL-MM-DD, kar omogoča enostavno "
"razvrščanje. Standardni &kde; izbirnik datuma lahko uporabite za izbiro "
"datuma z miško ali pa ga vnesete neposredno. Ni treba, da polje vsebuje "
"neprazne vrednosti za leto, mesec in dan; vpiše se lahko npr. samo letnica. "
"Več vrednosti ni dovoljeno."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid "Table"
msgstr "Tabela"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Table</emphasis> fields hold a one or more columns of values. In "
"the <link linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>Entry Editor</interface></"
"link>, the field is presented using a spreadsheet-like view, with numbered "
"rows. When the last row is selected, an additional row is then added. Auto-"
"completion is not available. This field is useful for a list of chapters in "
"a book, scenes in a movie, or songs in an album. <emphasis>Table</emphasis> "
"fields are always a category by themselves."
msgstr ""
"Polja <emphasis>tabele</emphasis> vsebujejo enega ali več stolpcev "
"vrednosti. V <link linkend=\"entry-editor\"><interface>urejevalniku vnosov</"
"interface></link> je polje predstavljeno v pogledu, podobnem preglednici, z "
"oštevilčenimi vrsticami. Ko je izbrana zadnja vrstica, se doda dodatna "
"vrstica. Samodokončanje ni na voljo. To polje je uporabno za seznam poglavij "
"v knjigi, prizorov v filmu ali pesmi v albumu. Polja <emphasis>tabele</"
"emphasis> so vedno kategorija zase."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:135
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of columns, up to a maximum of ten, is defined by adding a "
"property to the field definition with the name <emphasis>columns</emphasis>. "
"The columns may be labeled by right-clicking on the header, or by setting a "
"field property named <emphasis>column1</emphasis>, etc."
msgstr ""
"Število stolpcev, do največ deset, določite tako, da definiciji polja dodate "
"lastnost z imenom <emphasis>stolpci</emphasis>. Stolpce lahko označite z "
"desnim klikom na glavo ali z nastavitvijo lastnosti polja z imenom "
"<emphasis>column1</emphasis> itd."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the <interface>Entry Editor</interface> for <emphasis>Table</"
"emphasis> fields, rows may be rearranged by dragging the mouse while holding "
"the &Ctrl; button. A popup menu is also available by right-clicking on the "
"table, which allows rows to be inserted or removed."
msgstr ""
"Ko uporabljate <interface>Urejevalnik vnosov</interface> za polja "
"<emphasis>Tabela</emphasis>, lahko vrstice prerazporedite tako, da povlečete "
"miško, medtem ko držite &Ctrl; gumb. Pojavni meni je na voljo tudi z desnim "
"klikom na tabelo, ki omogoča vstavljanje ali odstranjevanje vrstic."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Image"
msgstr "Slika"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Image</emphasis> fields hold an image, of any format supported by "
"&kde;. Some of the typical ones include <acronym>PNG</acronym> or "
"<acronym>JPEG</acronym>. The image can be saved inside the &appname; data "
"file itself or in the application data directory. The standard &kde; File "
"Selector is used, so you can use a &URL; or just a file available locally. "
"Images can also be dragged from a file manager or browser."
msgstr ""
"Polja <emphasis>Slika</emphasis> vsebujejo sliko katere koli oblike, ki jo "
"podpira &kde;. Nekateri tipični vključujejo <acronym>PNG</acronym> ali "
"<acronym>JPEG</acronym>. Sliko lahko shranite znotraj &appname; sama "
"podatkovna datoteka ali v imeniku podatkov aplikacije. Standardni &kde; "
"Uporablja se izbirnik datotek, tako da lahko uporabite &URL; ali samo "
"datoteka, ki je na voljo lokalno. Slike lahko povlečete tudi iz upravitelja "
"datotek ali brskalnika."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rating"
msgstr "Ocena"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:165
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<emphasis>Rating</emphasis> fields show a number of stars to represent a "
"numerical rating for an entry. By default, the rating is a maximum of five. "
"The minimum and maximum may be changed by setting properties in the field "
"definition in the <interface>Collection Fields Dialog</interface>, named "
"<emphasis>minimum</emphasis> and <emphasis>maximum</emphasis>, respectively."
msgstr ""
"Polja <emphasis>Ocena</emphasis> prikazujejo število zvezdic, ki "
"predstavljajo številčno oceno vnosa. Privzeto je ocena največ pet. Najmanjšo "
"in največjo vrednost lahko spremenite z nastavitvijo lastnosti v definiciji "
"polja v <interface>pogovornem oknu zbirnih polj</interface>, imenovanih "
"<emphasis>minimum</emphasis> oziroma <emphasis>maximum</emphasis>."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:175
#, no-c-format
msgid "Derived Value Fields"
msgstr "Polja izpeljane vrednosti"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Fields with derived values are a special case. The field type corresponds to "
"the typical type of value contained in the field, but the value of the field "
"is constructed from other fields using a format string in the field "
"description. For example, if the field has a value template of <userinput>"
"%{title} %{year}</userinput>, then the value of that field will be the "
"title, followed by the year. This field type is used primarily for the title "
"field in the coin, stamp, trading card, and wine collections. Either the "
"internal field name or the field title may be used in the description for "
"formatting."
msgstr ""
"Polja z izpeljanimi vrednostmi so poseben primer. Vrsta polja ustreza "
"tipičnemu tipu vrednosti v polju, vendar je vrednost polja sestavljena iz "
"drugih polj z uporabo formatnega niza v opisu polja. Na primer, če ima polje "
"predlogo vrednosti <userinput>%{title} %{year}</userinput>, bo vrednost tega "
"polja naslov, ki mu sledi leto. Ta vrsta polja se uporablja predvsem za "
"naslovno polje v zbirkah kovancev, znamk, menjalnih kartic in vin. V opisu "
"za oblikovanje se lahko uporabi ime notranjega polja ali naslov polja."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:187
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To select only a single value for a field with multiple values, add a "
"position index to the template, such as <userinput>%{author:1}</userinput> "
"for the first author. The position may be negative, counting from the end, "
"so <userinput>%{author:-1}</userinput> would be the last author. Upper and "
"lower-case values may be used by setting template flags, such as <userinput>"
"%{author:1/l}</userinput> for lower-case first author and <userinput>"
"%{author:1/u}</userinput> for upper-case."
msgstr ""
"Če želite izbrati samo eno vrednost za polje z več vrednostmi, dodajte "
"indeks položaja v predlogo, kot je <userinput>%{author:1}</userinput> za "
"prvega avtorja. Položaj je lahko negativen, šteto od konca, tako da bi bil "
"<userinput>%{author:-1}</userinput> zadnji avtor. Vrednosti z velikimi in "
"malimi črkami se lahko uporabljajo z nastavitvijo zastavic predloge, kot je "
"<userinput>%{author:1/l}</userinput> za prvega avtorja z malimi črkami in "
"<userinput>%{author:1/u}</userinput> za velike črke."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:200
#, no-c-format
msgid "Collection Types"
msgstr "Vrste zbirk"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:202
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&appname; supports twelve specific collection types by default: books, "
"bibliographic entries, comic books, videos, music, video games, trading "
"cards, coins, stamps, wines, board games, and file catalogs. In addition, an "
"empty generic collection template is available for any other collectibles. "
"The default collections are only meant to include a general set of fields. "
"You should add, modify, or delete them to fit your needs. The only "
"requirement is that a collection should always have a <emphasis>Title</"
"emphasis> field, so that the <link linkend=\"group-view\"><interface>Group "
"View</interface></link> works correctly. For some collection types, that is "
"just a <link linkend=\"derived\">derived value</link> field combining two or "
"more of the others."
msgstr ""
"&appname; privzeto podpira dvanajst posebnih vrst zbirk: knjige, "
"bibliografske vnose, stripe, videoposnetke, glasbo, video igre, menjalne "
"karte, kovance, znamke, vina, družabne igre in kataloge datotek. Poleg tega "
"je prazna generična predloga zbirke na voljo za vse druge zbirateljske "
"predmete. Privzete zbirke naj bi vključevale le splošen nabor polj. Dodajte, "
"spremenite ali izbrišite jih, da bodo ustrezali vašim potrebam. Edina "
"zahteva je, da mora zbirka vedno imeti polje <emphasis>Naslov</emphasis>, "
"tako da <link linkend=\"group-view\"><interface>Pogled skupine</interface></"
"link> deluje pravilno. Pri nekaterih vrstah zbirk je to samo polje <link "
"linkend=\"derived\">izpeljane vrednosti</link>, ki združuje dve ali več "
"drugih."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:206
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In general, there's no functional difference between the collection types. "
"You could create a custom collection for your books just as easily as using "
"the default book collection. But &appname; chooses icons based on collection "
"type, and there may be some specialized functionality that is unique to a "
"certain collection, so if you can, you should use the defaults. So, if you "
"want to create a wine collection, but don't like any of the default fields, "
"go ahead and create a default wine collection, then delete all the defaults. "
"That way, &appname; still knows that it's a wine collection."
msgstr ""
"Na splošno ni funkcionalnih razlik med vrstami zbirk. Zbirko po meri za "
"svoje knjige lahko ustvarite prav tako preprosto kot s privzeto zbirko "
"knjig. Ampak &appname; izbere ikone glede na vrsto zbirke in morda obstaja "
"nekaj specializiranih funkcij, ki so edinstvene za določeno zbirko, tako da, "
"če lahko, uporabite privzete vrednosti. Torej, če želite ustvariti zbirko "
"vin, vendar vam ni všeč nobeno od privzetih polj, nadaljujte in ustvarite "
"privzeto zbirko vin, nato pa izbrišite vse privzete vrednosti. Na ta način "
"&appname; še vedno ve, da je zbirka vin."

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:210
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By default, all the collection types include an <emphasis>ID</emphasis> "
"field, which shows the ID number of the entry. In addition, except for the "
"file catalog, each collection includes fields showing the date that the "
"entry was created in the collection and the last time that it was modified."
msgstr ""
"Privzeto vse vrste zbirk vključujejo polje <emphasis>ID</emphasis>, ki "
"prikazuje ID številko vnosa. Poleg tega vsaka zbirka razen kataloga datotek "
"vključuje polja, ki prikazujejo datum, ko je bil vnos ustvarjen v zbirki, in "
"čas, ko je bil zadnjič spremenjen."

#. Tag: title
#: details.docbook:215
#, no-c-format
msgid "Book Collections"
msgstr "Knjižne zbirke"

#. Tag: para
#: details.docbook:216
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Book collections have 27 default fields: <emphasis>Title</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Subtitle</emphasis>, <emphasis>Author</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Binding</emphasis>, <emphasis>Purchase Date</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Purchase Price</emphasis>, <emphasis>Publisher</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Edition</emphasis>, <emphasis>Copyright Year</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Publication Year</emphasis>, <emphasis>ISBN#</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>LCCN#</emphasis>, <emphasis>Pages</emphasis>, <emphasis>Language</"
"emphasis>, <emphasis>Genre</emphasis>, <emphasis>Keywords</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Series</emphasis>, <emphasis>Series Number</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Condition</emphasis>, <emphasis>Signed</emphasis>, <emphasis>Read</"
"emphasis>, <emphasis>Gift</emphasis>, <emphasis>Loaned</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Rating</emphasis>, <emphasis>Front Cover</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Plot Summary</emphasis>, and <emphasis>Comments</emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"Knjižne zbirke imajo 27 privzetih polj: <emphasis>Naslov</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Podnaslov</emphasis>, <emphasis>Avtor</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Vezava</emphasis>, <emphasis>Datum nakupa</emphasis>, "
"<emphasis>Nakupna cena</emphasis>, <emphasis>Založnik</emphasis>, "
